2026-07-17 | Probe theories p1..p6 (authored minimal .spthy inputs) to find the trigger
  p1 In(x)->Out(x): NO warning (bare var derivable).
  p2a In(h(<zz,aa,mm>)) / p2b In(h(zz)),In(h(aa)),In(h(mm)): warn vars "aa, mm, zz"
     -> reported ALPHABETICALLY, not source order.
  p3 Fr(~x)->Out(~x): NO warning (fresh bound by Fr is derivable).
  p4 In(<a,b>)->Out(<a,b>): NO warning (pair invertible via fst/snd).
  p6 In(skf(x)), skf private: warn "x".

2026-07-17 | Probes o1..o4 (sort semantics, rule order, no_derivcheck)
  o1 In(h(<v10,v2,v1>)): "v1, v10, v2" -> name compared LEXICOGRAPHICALLY (string).
  o2 In(h(x)),In(h($p)),In(h(~n)): "~n, x" -> $p (public) EXCLUDED; ~n before x.
  o3 rule Zebra; rule Apple: reported "Rule Zebra" then "Rule Apple" -> THEORY(source) order.
  o4 rule R [no_derivcheck] In(h(x)): NO warning -> attribute suppresses the rule.

2026-07-17 | Probes s1..s4 (sort key disambiguation, index, candidate scope, mixed)
  s1 In(h(aaa)),In(h(~zzz)): "~zzz, aaa" -> SORT-TAG dominates name (Fresh < Msg);
     name-first would give aaa first, so key is (sort, name, idx).
  s2 In(h(<x.1,x.10,x.2>)): "x.1, x.2, x.10" -> index compared NUMERICALLY.
  s3 rule Use [St(x),In(h(y))]: only "y" -> state-fact var x is derivable (not flagged);
     only intruder-supplied (In) content matters.
  s4 rule Good In(x)->Out(x); rule Bad In(h(w)): only "Rule Bad: w" -> derivable rules omitted.

